gw.api.builder

Class SubmissionBuilderBase<B extends SubmissionBuilderBase<B>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,B>
      • gw.api.builder.JobBuilder<B>
        • gw.api.builder.SubmissionBuilderBase<B>
  • Type Parameters:
    B - Type of builder itself, needed for return type of methods that return "this"
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExtendedMultiQuoteJobBuilder, IMultiQuoteJobBuilder, ValueGenerator<PolicyPeriod>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SubmissionBuilder

    public class SubmissionBuilderBase<B extends SubmissionBuilderBase<B>>
extends JobBuilder<B>
implements ExtendedMultiQuoteJobBuilder
    Base builder class for creating a PolicyCenter submission. The simplest possible use of this class would be 
       new SubmissionBuilderBase().createAndCommit()
    which would create a new Account held by a new Person, and use that to create a bound-and-issued policy, effective today, with default producer and billing options. To create a different line of business you would need to specify the product code, the line code, and a variety of other lob-specific information. For convenience, it is common to define a LOB-specific submission builder as part of creating the content for that LOB.

    The builder will attempt to supply defaults for any necessary information that was not supplied. When DataBuilder.create() is called, this class' method createBean(BuilderContext) is invoked. If producer or account were not specified, it will fill them in at that time, as follows:

    • Producer = (if TinyCommunityData is loaded and unmodified)
    • Account = (a newly-created AccountBuilder, with a new PersonBuilder for its AccountHolderContact)
    • Line-level clauses (Coverages, Conditions and Exclusions) will be created.
    After create is called, BeanPopulators are run. Some of these are inherited from JobBuilder. SubmissionBuilderBase defines a populator which runs at JobBuilder.POSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_2. It sets up much of the data specific to this builder. During the run of this populator, some other things are also done:
    • policyPeriod.getEffectiveDatedFields().updateModifiers() is called
    • If the submission is a WC policy, WC jurisdictions are created
    • policyPeriod.syncComputedValues() is called
    • PrimaryNamedInsured, if not specified, will be created from the main account contact
    • OfficialIDs are validated for all Named Insureds.

      • makeProducerSelectionForSubmission

        public ProducerSelection makeProducerSelectionForSubmission(Bundle bundle,
                                                            java.lang.String orgName)
        Helper which finds a ProducerSelection corresponding to the given orgName. Build a new ProducerCode if necessary, using a new ProducerCodeBuilder with a default producer code. If the producer organization has been set on the SubmissionBuilder, use that for the producer organization and branch; otherwise use the new one created by the ProducerCodeBuilder.
        Parameters:
        bundle - The bundle to be used when searching for the Organization
        orgName - The name of the desired organization
        Returns:
        A ProducerSelection containing a producer and producer code for the organization.
